This paper discusses techniques for estimating the size of views in data warehouses, which is a common problem in the field of database management (cs.DB). The techniques used are probabilistic and involve hashing, which are also commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the accuracy and reliability of these techniques, which are important considerations in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
